00:31:49,820 --> 00:31:51,890
<b>(Announcements, Introduction, List of New Books, Requests)</b>

375
00:31:51,890 --> 00:31:53,030
<b>(Bookstore Diary)</b>

376
00:31:56,460 --> 00:31:58,060
<b>(Bookstore Diary)</b>

377
00:31:58,060 --> 00:32:00,500
<b>(My first love letter to you, the 133rd post)</b>

378
00:32:05,100 --> 00:32:09,210
<b>(Tonight, I want to take you to the cottage...)</b>

379
00:32:43,070 --> 00:32:44,610
<b>Hae Won.</b>

380
00:32:55,850 --> 00:32:57,260
<b>Hae Won?</b>

381
00:33:02,290 --> 00:33:05,430
<b>Hae Won. What are you...</b>

382
00:33:07,460 --> 00:33:08,670
<b>Hey!</b>

383
00:33:10,730 --> 00:33:12,910
<b>Irene was me?</b>

384
00:33:15,340 --> 00:33:16,740
<b>You said it was Hwi.</b>

385
00:33:18,570 --> 00:33:21,020
<b>Then was that key chain really from me?</b>

386
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,680
<b>No. How...</b>

387
00:33:23,210 --> 00:33:24,710
<b>How much did you read?</b>

388
00:33:24,710 --> 00:33:26,450
<b>Then what does "Good night, Irene" mean?</b>

389
00:33:26,450 --> 00:33:27,520
<b>No.</b>

390
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:30,350
<b>That's just from some lyrics of a song that I like.</b>

391
00:33:30,350 --> 00:33:32,150
<b>- Why am I Irene? - That's because...</b>

392
00:33:32,150 --> 00:33:33,450
<b>you gave me that key chain.</b>

393
00:33:33,450 --> 00:33:35,460
<b>But you said you made it.</b>

394
00:33:42,930 --> 00:33:46,770
<b>I didn't know you kept a diary, Eun Seop. How cute.</b>

395
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:51,080
<b>Can you tell me how much you read?</b>

396
00:33:52,540 --> 00:33:53,710
<b>I'm not sure.</b>

397
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:57,450
<b>So you were the one who gave me that bug when we were young.</b>

398
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:06,190
<b>- I don't want this. - What?</b>

399
00:34:06,190 --> 00:34:08,200
<b>I don't want this. Take it back. Now.</b>

400
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:14,000
<b>That's because I thought you were a boy.</b>

401
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,860
<b>What? Why? Why did you think I was a boy?</b>

402
00:34:16,860 --> 00:34:19,400
<b>Because you were covering your face with a hat.</b>

403
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:22,440
<b>What? Goodness. This is unbelievable.</b>

404
00:34:22,670 --> 00:34:24,380
<b>Oh, and...</b>

405
00:34:24,770 --> 00:34:27,250
<b>you even slept at my house.</b>

406
00:34:41,290 --> 00:34:42,560
<b>Who...</b>

407
00:34:43,220 --> 00:34:44,870
<b>are you?</b>

408
00:34:45,490 --> 00:34:48,700
<b>That's because Hwi suddenly got sick.</b>

409
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:51,870
<b>My parents took her to a hospital in Seoul so I had to sleep over.</b>

410
00:34:51,870 --> 00:34:56,040
<b>So that's why you fell in love again with a fairy like me.</b>

411
00:34:56,470 --> 00:34:58,150
<b>This is so fun, Eun Seop.</b>

412
00:35:01,580 --> 00:35:03,740
<b>- Did you read all of it? - Of course not.</b>

413
00:35:03,740 --> 00:35:05,320
<b>Almost all of it.</b>

414
00:35:08,050 --> 00:35:11,090
<b>Now I finally know the secret of the Nakdong River incident.</b>

415
00:35:11,090 --> 00:35:13,890
<b>I was baffled by the timing my aunt came for me.</b>

416
00:35:14,020 --> 00:35:15,930
<b>You were the one who called her.</b>

417
00:35:17,790 --> 00:35:21,100
<b>I didn't even know that and almost believed in fate.</b>

418
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:22,370
<b>Gosh.</b>

419
00:35:24,470 --> 00:35:27,340
<b>It's all right, Eun Seop. I won't tease you.</b>

420
00:35:27,340 --> 00:35:30,080
<b>My lips are sealed. Come on, don't be so sad.</b>

421
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:32,140
<b>- I'm ruined. - Eun Seop.</b>

422
00:35:32,140 --> 00:35:33,280
<b>What?</b>

423
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:36,240
<b>- "That day, Irene asked." - Stop.</b>

424
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:37,750
<b>- "Over there." - I said, stop.</b>

425
00:35:37,750 --> 00:35:39,350
<b>"Those things that look like marshmallows."</b>

426
00:35:39,350 --> 00:35:42,560
<b>- Be quiet! No, Stop! - "What are they called?"</b>

427
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:46,690
<b>Wait.</b>

428
00:35:47,050 --> 00:35:49,100
<b>Yes, this is Good Night Bookstore.</b>

429
00:35:49,690 --> 00:35:50,870
<b>What?</b>

430
00:35:57,670 --> 00:36:00,870
<b>(Hyecheon Station)</b>

431
00:36:00,870 --> 00:36:02,840
<b>What are you doing here again?</b>

432
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:05,910
<b>You told me about the train schedule.</b>

433
00:36:06,470 --> 00:36:07,720
<b>Yun Taek.</b>

434
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:11,190
<b>I lost hope.</b>

435
00:36:11,510 --> 00:36:13,290
<b>I have nothing left now.</b>

436
00:36:13,810 --> 00:36:17,290
<b>So don't expect anything from me.</b>

437
00:36:18,250 --> 00:36:19,560
<b>Shim Myeong Yeo.</b>

438
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:26,000
<b>Your hair...</b>

439
00:36:26,860 --> 00:36:30,910
<b>smelled like the "Charming" shampoo my mom used to use.</b>

440
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:51,830
<b>And your eyes...</b>

441
00:36:52,690 --> 00:36:56,100
<b>reminded me of the night before a rainstorm.</b>

442
00:36:59,830 --> 00:37:01,670
<b>I really loved that about you.</b>

443
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:07,440
<b>Can you tell me?</b>

444
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:11,710
<b>That none of it is true?</b>

445
00:37:14,580 --> 00:37:15,880
<b>What's not true?</b>

446
00:37:15,880 --> 00:37:17,150
<b>Everything.</b>

447
00:37:17,380 --> 00:37:19,680
<b>Oh, the rumor that my sister killed her husband...</b>

448
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:22,090
<b>because he had an affair with me?</b>

449
00:37:23,780 --> 00:37:24,930
<b>Well...</b>

450
00:37:25,590 --> 00:37:27,430
<b>People can believe what they want to believe.</b>

451
00:37:28,020 --> 00:37:30,200
<b>The outcome won't change regardless of what you believe.</b>

452
00:37:30,490 --> 00:37:32,690
<b>Whether I had an affair with my brother-in-law or not,</b>

453
00:37:32,690 --> 00:37:34,570
<b>he died, and that won't change.</b>

454
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:37,670
<b>And whether my sister killed him or not,</b>

455
00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:40,740
<b>she went to jail.</b>

456
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:43,410
<b>And even if she didn't go to jail,</b>

457
00:37:43,840 --> 00:37:45,910
<b>I'd still be the mess that I am today.</b>

458
00:37:47,410 --> 00:37:50,140
<b>So it doesn't matter. Whatever you believe is the truth.</b>

459
00:37:50,140 --> 00:37:51,750
<b>- No. - Yes.</b>

460
00:37:52,780 --> 00:37:54,390
<b>That is the truth,</b>

461
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:56,020
<b>Cha Yun Taek.</b>

462
00:38:02,420 --> 00:38:06,770
<b>(Hyecheon Station)</b>

463
00:38:06,990 --> 00:38:09,040
<b>Even if that is the truth,</b>

464
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:13,310
<b>you should tell me that it isn't.</b>

465
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:16,980
<b>That's the least you can do for me. Am I wrong?</b>

466
00:38:20,470 --> 00:38:21,620
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

467
00:38:23,240 --> 00:38:24,890
<b>I'm inconsiderate, you know.</b>

468
00:38:27,250 --> 00:38:28,620
<b>Myeong Yeo.</b>

469
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:31,490
<b>I...</b>

470
00:38:35,660 --> 00:38:36,860
<b>I have...</b>

471
00:38:39,460 --> 00:38:41,070
<b>wilted.</b>

472
00:38:41,460 --> 00:38:43,770
<b>We all have.</b>

473
00:38:44,930 --> 00:38:47,270
<b>I've wilted as much as you have.</b>

474
00:38:59,010 --> 00:39:00,220
<b>Come on.</b>

475
00:39:01,020 --> 00:39:03,060
<b>I'm the only one who has completely wilted.</b>

476
00:39:04,290 --> 00:39:05,530
<b>I'm the only one...</b>

477
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:10,200
<b>who's totally dead, Yun Taek.</b>

478
00:39:28,810 --> 00:39:30,910
<b>"I will cut off the tips of my five fingers..."</b>

479
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:32,790
<b>"and draw a staff with my blood."</b>

480
00:39:33,110 --> 00:39:35,050
<b>"I will be alone tonight, but I won't be lonely."</b>

481
00:39:35,050 --> 00:39:36,360
<b>"And tonight, I will shed tears."</b>

482
00:39:39,690 --> 00:39:43,000
<b>"The first glass is for you, who left me."</b>

483
00:39:46,260 --> 00:39:50,640
<b>"The second glass is for me, who is already so pathetic."</b>

484
00:39:54,070 --> 00:39:58,080
<b>"Another glass for our eternal love."</b>

485
00:40:01,040 --> 00:40:02,180
<b>"And..."</b>

486
00:40:03,180 --> 00:40:06,920
<b>"the last glass is for the Almighty who foresaw..."</b>

487
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,690
<b>"and decided everything in advance."</b>

488
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:12,990
<b>(Good Night Bookstore)</b>

489
00:40:13,890 --> 00:40:15,790
<b>Hello, I'm Ji Eun Sil.</b>

490
00:40:15,790 --> 00:40:17,360
<b>I work at Gangneung City Hall.</b>

491
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:18,960
<b>I'm taking some time off work...</b>

492
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:19,990
<b>because of the event.</b>

493
00:40:19,990 --> 00:40:21,660
<b>That's why I'm here today.</b>

494
00:40:21,660 --> 00:40:22,800
<b>Applause!</b>

495
00:40:25,870 --> 00:40:27,970
<b>My gosh, a number of new members...</b>

496
00:40:27,970 --> 00:40:30,340
<b>have joined us recently.</b>

497
00:40:30,340 --> 00:40:31,540
<b>It's encouraging.</b>

498
00:40:31,540 --> 00:40:34,680
<b>Jang Woo, you look a little spaced out today.</b>

499
00:40:34,680 --> 00:40:36,920
<b>Me? No, I'm not.</b>

500
00:40:36,980 --> 00:40:38,480
<b>- Jang Woo. - Yes.</b>

501
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:40,450
<b>Did you drink something hot?</b>

502
00:40:40,450 --> 00:40:43,520
<b>No, I only drink iced Americano.</b>

503
00:41:03,540 --> 00:41:05,770
<b>"When I realized I hadn't had a chance to tell you..."</b>

504
00:41:05,770 --> 00:41:08,810
<b>"that I loved you with all my heart,"</b>

505
00:41:08,810 --> 00:41:11,850
<b>"you were already in love with someone else."</b>

506
00:41:12,180 --> 00:41:15,020
<b>"I silenced the passionate serenade inside my heart..."</b>

507
00:41:15,020 --> 00:41:17,960
<b>"as you drifted far away from me."</b>

508
00:41:18,220 --> 00:41:21,190
<b>"You told me to forget everything..."</b>

509
00:41:21,190 --> 00:41:24,370
<b>"before your pretty smile vanished and only remember your beauty,"</b>

510
00:41:24,390 --> 00:41:25,990
<b>"but to a man,"</b>

511
00:41:25,990 --> 00:41:28,540
<b>"a woman either signifies joy or sorrow."</b>

512
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:31,510
<b>"Love" by Cho Chi Hun.</b>

513
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:34,170
<b>What's that?</b>

514
00:41:34,300 --> 00:41:36,340
<b>It's a poem.</b>

515
00:41:37,910 --> 00:41:41,020
<b>It makes my heart ache every time I hear it.</b>

516
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:43,550
<b>Why does your heart ache, Auntie?</b>

517
00:41:43,740 --> 00:41:46,590
<b>Is love painful?</b>

518
00:41:46,980 --> 00:41:48,320
<b>Well...</b>

519
00:41:48,750 --> 00:41:51,490
<b>For me, no. But I'm not sure.</b>

520
00:41:52,550 --> 00:41:56,600
<b>Jang Woo, is love painful for you?</b>

521
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:03,670
<b>Did your crush who rejected you...</b>

522
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,210
<b>break your heart?</b>

523
00:42:06,130 --> 00:42:07,200
<b>Eun Seop, get me some tissue.</b>

524
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:09,080
<b>I'll bring it.</b>

525
00:42:10,070 --> 00:42:11,210
<b>What's wrong?</b>

526
00:42:11,510 --> 00:42:13,180
<b>- Hae Won went to grab it? - Yes.</b>

527
00:42:31,560 --> 00:42:32,700
<b>(Bookstore Diary)</b>

528
00:42:37,870 --> 00:42:39,140
<b>(The 130th Story)</b>

529
00:42:39,470 --> 00:42:41,000
<b>(The Bookstore in the Ocean)</b>

530
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,910
<b>(Hae Won, I understand that you will leave this place one day.)</b>

531
00:42:44,940 --> 00:42:46,080
<b>Hae Won.</b>

532
00:42:47,170 --> 00:42:48,580
<b>I understand...</b>

533
00:42:49,310 --> 00:42:51,820
<b>that you will leave this place one day.</b>

534
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:58,660
<b>Hae Won.</b>

535
00:42:59,250 --> 00:43:01,530
<b>- Yes. - Hae Won, someone's on the phone.</b>

536
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:03,060
<b>Who?</b>

537
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:04,970
<b>She said her name is Bo Yeong.</b>

538
00:43:07,560 --> 00:43:08,700
<b>Oh, okay.</b>

539
00:43:11,270 --> 00:43:12,410
<b>Well...</b>

540
00:43:12,870 --> 00:43:14,870
<b>I think Jang Woo was probably...</b>

541
00:43:14,870 --> 00:43:16,270
<b>No, no way.</b>

542
00:43:16,270 --> 00:43:18,870
<b>No, I've never been heartbroken because of love.</b>

543
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:20,810
<b>I swear...</b>

544
00:43:20,810 --> 00:43:23,650
<b>on the rice field road where I walk every single day.</b>

545
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:26,410
<b>But one-sided love is sad.</b>

546
00:43:26,410 --> 00:43:28,520
<b>- Hey. - That's what I learned from books.</b>

547
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:30,250
<b>- Hey. - Seung Ho.</b>

548
00:43:30,250 --> 00:43:31,650
<b>You know so many things.</b>

549
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:33,690
<b>Seung Ho, do you have a girlfriend?</b>

550
00:43:33,690 --> 00:43:34,820
<b>No, I don't.</b>

551
00:43:34,820 --> 00:43:36,090
<b>The other day, you said you did.</b>

552
00:43:36,090 --> 00:43:38,330
<b>- No, that's not true. I didn't. - My gosh!</b>

553
00:43:38,330 --> 00:43:40,030
<b>- Who's this girl? - I don't have a girlfriend.</b>

554
00:43:40,030 --> 00:43:42,860
<b>- Your face is turning red. - I don't have one.</b>

555
00:43:42,860 --> 00:43:44,300
<b>I don't have a girlfriend.</b>

556
00:43:44,500 --> 00:43:46,170
<b>No, it's not true.</b>

557
00:43:46,570 --> 00:43:48,610
<b>- Why is your face beet red? - It's not.</b>

558
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:17,200
<b>Giddy up! Let's go!</b>

559
00:44:22,240 --> 00:44:23,940
<b>Faster!</b>

560
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,610
<b>Giddy up! Let's go!</b>

561
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:50,600
<b>Out of the way!</b>

562
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:52,800
<b>Hi!</b>

563
00:44:52,800 --> 00:44:54,880
<b>(Hyecheon High School)</b>

564
00:44:55,670 --> 00:44:57,440
<b>Hi!</b>

565
00:44:57,640 --> 00:44:59,250
<b>Oh, it's Hwi.</b>

566
00:44:59,440 --> 00:45:01,280
<b>Hi!</b>

567
00:45:03,010 --> 00:45:04,220
<b>Good morning, sir!</b>

568
00:45:16,020 --> 00:45:19,170
<b>What a beautiful morning.</b>

569
00:45:21,030 --> 00:45:26,100
<b>(Bukhyeon Three-way Intersection)</b>

570
00:45:26,100 --> 00:45:28,780
<b>(Bukhyeon-ri, Downtown Hyecheon, Seohyeon Village)</b>

571
00:45:52,260 --> 00:45:55,200
<b>I've never had anyone asking to meet up on the bus.</b>

572
00:45:58,870 --> 00:46:00,340
<b>What did you want to talk to me about?</b>

573
00:46:03,340 --> 00:46:05,910
<b>I thought about what you said.</b>

574
00:46:09,810 --> 00:46:12,790
<b>About how twisted I am.</b>

575
00:46:15,880 --> 00:46:19,030
<b>You're right. I was like that.</b>

576
00:46:20,290 --> 00:46:22,660
<b>I really hated you.</b>

577
00:46:24,190 --> 00:46:25,500
<b>I mean, think about it.</b>

578
00:46:26,160 --> 00:46:29,000
<b>You cut all ties with me after just one strike.</b>

579
00:46:29,430 --> 00:46:31,170
<b>Because of one mistake.</b>

580
00:46:31,230 --> 00:46:33,340
<b>You didn't even want to listen to me.</b>

581
00:46:34,370 --> 00:46:36,900
<b>Hae Won, just a moment.</b>

582
00:46:36,900 --> 00:46:38,110
<b>Let go!</b>

583
00:46:39,570 --> 00:46:42,420
<b>Hae Won!</b>

584
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:51,830
<b>No matter how hard I tried,</b>

585
00:46:52,120 --> 00:46:54,460
<b>you wouldn't even look at me.</b>

586
00:46:55,620 --> 00:46:59,490
<b>When I heard you were here, I went to see you.</b>

587
00:46:59,490 --> 00:47:00,800
<b>So?</b>

588
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:06,110
<b>Are you saying you still can't forgive me?</b>

589
00:47:08,300 --> 00:47:11,040
<b>So I started waiting.</b>

590
00:47:12,010 --> 00:47:13,450
<b>Waiting for what?</b>

591
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:16,410
<b>For your forgiveness...</b>

592
00:47:16,410 --> 00:47:18,890
<b>to become overdue.</b>

593
00:47:19,850 --> 00:47:22,960
<b>Then you'd become a petty and cold person,</b>

594
00:47:23,520 --> 00:47:25,550
<b>and I'd become this miserable person,</b>

595
00:47:25,550 --> 00:47:28,400
<b>who is pitied by everyone.</b>

596
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:35,070
<b>"One strike"?</b>

597
00:47:36,960 --> 00:47:38,140
<b>Bo Yeong.</b>

598
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:41,710
<b>It might have been one strike for you,</b>

599
00:47:42,240 --> 00:47:44,310
<b>but for me, it was a strikeout.</b>

600
00:47:44,910 --> 00:47:47,940
<b>I told you the biggest secret of my life,</b>

601
00:47:47,940 --> 00:47:50,320
<b>and you didn't keep it to yourself.</b>

602
00:47:51,680 --> 00:47:54,110
<b>You might try to defend yourself...</b>

603
00:47:54,110 --> 00:47:55,780
<b>by saying you only told Joo Hee,</b>

604
00:47:55,780 --> 00:47:57,420
<b>but because you told that one person...</b>

605
00:47:57,420 --> 00:47:59,760
<b>I didn't think of it like that.</b>

606
00:48:03,860 --> 00:48:05,200
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

607
00:48:11,570 --> 00:48:13,370
<b>But I...</b>

608
00:48:13,770 --> 00:48:17,780
<b>couldn't help thinking it was just one mistake.</b>

609
00:48:19,140 --> 00:48:21,150
<b>So I hated you.</b>

610
00:48:27,010 --> 00:48:30,520
<b>I'm sure you didn't hate me. You just disliked me.</b>

611
00:48:31,220 --> 00:48:33,760
<b>- Are they different? - Yes.</b>

612
00:48:34,190 --> 00:48:35,500
<b>They are.</b>

613
00:48:36,520 --> 00:48:39,600
<b>You can dislike anyone,</b>

614
00:48:40,690 --> 00:48:43,770
<b>but you can only hate someone you like.</b>

615
00:48:47,230 --> 00:48:49,580
<b>I really liked you.</b>

616
00:48:49,740 --> 00:48:52,580
<b>Attention. We have a new transfer student.</b>

617
00:48:54,810 --> 00:48:57,840
<b>Her name is Mok Hae Won. She's from Seoul.</b>

618
00:48:57,840 --> 00:49:01,320
<b>You know the mock exam is next week, right?</b>

619
00:49:01,450 --> 00:49:04,320
<b>- Let's try to score... - She's pretty.</b>

620
00:49:04,320 --> 00:49:07,830
<b>A mill and a guesthouse...</b>

621
00:49:08,360 --> 00:49:09,730
<b>are different?</b>

622
00:49:12,030 --> 00:49:13,270
<b>Gosh.</b>

623
00:49:13,760 --> 00:49:17,040
<b>You're very sweet.</b>

624
00:49:18,300 --> 00:49:20,070
<b>That must have been why...</b>

625
00:49:20,170 --> 00:49:22,480
<b>I kept trying so hard and going to see you.</b>

626
00:49:27,980 --> 00:49:32,350
<b>Even if you decided to dislike me...</b>

627
00:49:32,850 --> 00:49:36,020
<b>and never to give me a second chance...</b>

628
00:49:36,950 --> 00:49:39,460
<b>because you only cared about me that much.</b>

629
00:50:17,420 --> 00:50:20,530
<b>Hi, I'm Kim Bo Yeong. Nice to meet you.</b>

630
00:50:20,530 --> 00:50:21,840
<b>Hae Won.</b>

631
00:50:23,660 --> 00:50:25,410
<b>Do you want to team up with me?</b>

632
00:50:28,340 --> 00:50:29,780
<b>You can use this.</b>

633
00:50:31,370 --> 00:50:33,910
<b>I live close by, so I can just run home.</b>

634
00:50:35,880 --> 00:50:38,490
<b>Kim Bo Yeong... Bo Yeong.</b>

635
00:50:39,610 --> 00:50:41,790
<b>See you tomorrow, Hae Won!</b>

636
00:50:43,480 --> 00:50:45,160
<b>Bo Yeong!</b>

637
00:50:46,850 --> 00:50:48,030
<b>This...</b>

638
00:51:01,170 --> 00:51:04,240
<b>(Good Night Bookstore)</b>

639
00:51:15,380 --> 00:51:16,720
<b>Hello?</b>

640
00:51:22,490 --> 00:51:25,000
<b>Mr. Jung Gil Bok?</b>

641
00:51:32,730 --> 00:51:34,370
<b>Hello. I'm...</b>

642
00:51:34,370 --> 00:51:36,180
<b>Wait here for a second.</b>

643
00:51:39,210 --> 00:51:41,980
<b>I'm here to see Mr. Jung Gil Bok.</b>

644
00:51:41,980 --> 00:51:44,020
<b>Fill this out, please.</b>

645
00:51:44,380 --> 00:51:47,410
<b>His neighbor found him on the street and brought him here.</b>

646
00:51:47,410 --> 00:51:50,590
<b>It's nothing serious, but he should stay in the hospital for a few days.</b>

647
00:51:50,950 --> 00:51:54,720
<b>But he's insisting on going home.</b>

648
00:51:54,720 --> 00:51:57,560
<b>I think he's worried about the hospital bills.</b>

649
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:08,240
<b>Seung Ho.</b>

650
00:52:10,800 --> 00:52:12,710
<b>Uncle.</b>

651
00:52:24,220 --> 00:52:25,930
<b>Don't worry too much.</b>

652
00:52:34,690 --> 00:52:36,700
<b>He'll get better soon.</b>

653
00:52:39,200 --> 00:52:41,140
<b>We had...</b>

654
00:52:41,640 --> 00:52:43,440
<b>rabbits at school.</b>

655
00:52:43,640 --> 00:52:46,310
<b>- Run! - Wait for me!</b>

656
00:52:46,310 --> 00:52:48,340
<b>Hey, stop!</b>

657
00:52:48,340 --> 00:52:50,410
<b>Where are you going?</b>

658
00:52:50,410 --> 00:52:51,720
<b>Eat.</b>

659
00:52:52,110 --> 00:52:54,490
<b>They were so cute.</b>

660
00:52:56,950 --> 00:52:58,730
<b>But they died.</b>

661
00:53:02,220 --> 00:53:04,530
<b>What if the same thing happens...</b>

662
00:53:04,860 --> 00:53:07,800
<b>to my grandpa?</b>

663
00:53:12,570 --> 00:53:14,370
<b>He'll be fine.</b>

664
00:53:18,270 --> 00:53:20,110
<b>I promise you.</b>

665
00:53:54,870 --> 00:53:56,080
<b>I'll help you.</b>

666
00:53:58,910 --> 00:54:00,050
<b>There you go.</b>

667
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:55,280
<b>Yes, you should pat your face.</b>

668
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:58,210
<b>Under your eyes too.</b>

669
00:55:06,680 --> 00:55:08,920
<b>Pat, pat, pat...</b>

670
00:55:11,220 --> 00:55:13,950
<b>Auntie, can you take out some blankets later?</b>

671
00:55:13,950 --> 00:55:15,360
<b>I will, Ji Yeon,</b>

672
00:55:15,360 --> 00:55:18,100
<b>but I'm not Auntie. I'm Myeong Yeo.</b>

673
00:55:18,690 --> 00:55:20,160
<b>That's right.</b>

674
00:55:20,160 --> 00:55:22,000
<b>Call Myeong Yeo by her first name.</b>

675
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:24,100
<b>Don't call her Auntie.</b>

676
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:27,570
<b>Grow up. What's so bad about being called Auntie?</b>

677
00:55:27,570 --> 00:55:29,670
<b>Eun Seop's parents still treat you...</b>

678
00:55:29,670 --> 00:55:31,440
<b>like a high school girl.</b>

679
00:55:31,440 --> 00:55:32,840
<b>You graduated from high school years ago.</b>

680
00:55:32,840 --> 00:55:34,740
<b>That's because I still am like a high school girl.</b>

681
00:55:34,740 --> 00:55:37,910
<b>You do still have a high school girl's skin. What's your secret?</b>

682
00:55:37,910 --> 00:55:40,150
<b>I put something on just now.</b>

683
00:55:41,680 --> 00:55:43,990
<b>Seung Ho, what is that book?</b>

684
00:55:44,150 --> 00:55:45,990
<b>"Owl at Home".</b>

685
00:55:45,990 --> 00:55:47,390
<b>Can I see it too?</b>

686
00:55:47,490 --> 00:55:49,360
<b>Yes, of course.</b>

687
00:55:51,590 --> 00:55:53,960
<b>That's the story about Teardrop Tea.</b>

688
00:55:53,960 --> 00:55:55,030
<b>Yes.</b>

689
00:55:55,030 --> 00:55:59,470
<b>Whenever the owl thinks of something sad and cries,</b>

690
00:55:59,600 --> 00:56:01,330
<b>it gathers its teardrops in a kettle...</b>

691
00:56:01,330 --> 00:56:03,170
<b>and makes Teardrop Tea.</b>

692
00:56:03,170 --> 00:56:06,850
<b>It's a story about how the owl forgets about its sadness like that.</b>

693
00:56:07,410 --> 00:56:09,880
<b>Then shall we make Teardrop Tea too?</b>

694
00:56:10,040 --> 00:56:13,750
<b>Myeong Yeo, do you really have Teardrop Tea?</b>

695
00:56:13,750 --> 00:56:14,750
<b>Of course.</b>

696
00:56:14,750 --> 00:56:17,320
<b>Wait. You call Eun Seop an uncle...</b>

697
